# HRMS Security Rules

## Authentication

- JWT tokens for API authentication
- Store tokens securely (httpOnly cookies preferred)
- Implement refresh token rotation
- Set appropriate token expiration

## Authorization

- Use role-based access control (RBAC)
- Check permissions at API level
- Validate user claims on each request
- Implement policy-based authorization

## Data Protection

- Never log sensitive data (passwords, tokens)
- Hash passwords with BCrypt/Argon2
- Use HTTPS everywhere
- Validate all inputs
- Sanitize outputs to prevent XSS

## API Security

- Implement rate limiting
- Use CORS properly
- Add security headers (CSP, X-Frame-Options)
- Validate content-type headers
- Prevent SQL injection (use parameterized queries)

## Secrets Management

- Never commit secrets to git
- Use environment variables or secret managers
- Different configs for dev/staging/prod

## Common Vulnerabilities

- **SQL Injection**: Use EF Core parameterized queries
- **XSS**: Sanitize user inputs
- **CSRF**: Use anti-forgery tokens
- **IDOR**: Verify ownership before operations
